data.name: btn_arm_disarm.ToolTip
data.value: Arm or disarm the recorder. If the recorder is disarmed, no new records are started. When you disarm the recorder while it was recording, the current record is finished and then no new records are started. If the recorder is armed, new records are started, when spotify is playing (not paused) and the track is changing or the position is reset to 0.

data.name: cmb_fileExistMode.ToolTip
data.value: What should be done, if a file already exists: - SKIP: Don't record and wait for the next song - OVERWRITE: record again and overwrite the existing file - CREATENEW: record again and create a new file with an added number

data.name: txt_filename_prototype.ToolTip
data.value: The file name prototype is used to build the path where records are saved. You can insert custom informations and record dependent informations like the title or interpret. The record base path is used at the beginning of the the file path. If the file already exists, a number is added dependent on the selected option for existing files.
